<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="4" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
The name 
<taxonomicName class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Hemileia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hemileia hansfordii" order="Pucciniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="hansfordii">Hemileia hansfordii</taxonomicName>
Syd. has priority but was not used previously because of the lack of teliospores on the type specimen. 
<bibRefCitation author="Wakefield, EM" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Linnean Society of London" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="162 - 198" title="Contributions towards the fungus flora of Uganda. IX. The Uredinales of Uganda." url="10.1111/j.1095-8312.1949.tb00565.x" volume="161" year="1949">Wakefield and Hansford (1949)</bibRefCitation>
described a new name for this species when they found teliospores but their name was a later homonym of the existing 
<taxonomicName class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Hemileia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hemileia hansfordii" order="Pucciniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="hansfordii">Hemileia hansfordii</taxonomicName>
Syd. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ritschel, A" journalOrPublisher="Bibliotheca Mycologica" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 132" title="Monograph of the genus Hemileia (Uredinales)." volume="200" year="2005">Ritschel (2005)</bibRefCitation>
provided a new name for this species but that name, 
<taxonomicName class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Hemileia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hemileia wakefieldii" order="Pucciniales" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="wakefieldii">Hemileia wakefieldii</taxonomicName>
, is now considered a nomenclatural synonym because the oldest name is now legitimate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
